The **multiple-nuclei model** (proposed by Chauncey Harris and Edward Ullman) emphasizes that cities often have **multiple independent centers of activity** (e.g., commercial, industrial, or residential hubs) rather than a single central business district. This contrasts with the **concentric zone model**, which assumes a single core. Option D directly reflects this key feature of the theory.
